The article is a statement by the President of the United States, issued on June 8, 2009, regarding the death of President El Hadj Omar Bongo Ondimba of Gabon. The President expresses his sadness at the news and highlights President Bongo's role in developing the strong bilateral relationship between Gabon and the United States. He also mentions President Bongo's emphasis on compromise, peace, and conservation in Gabon, as well as his commitment to conflict resolution across the continent. The President offers his condolences to President Bongo's family and the people of Gabon on behalf of the United States government.